---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Financial | BeaconGuard for Regulated Financial Workflows"
  description="BeaconGuard enforces ALLOW or DENY decisions for AML, KYC, fraud, dispute, and customer-impacting financial workflows before governed execution."
>
  <section class="stack-section">
    <h1>Deterministic control for regulated financial workflows</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      BeaconGuard deploys alongside existing financial applications as a Runtime Control Boundary. It evaluates trusted request context against the Active Verified Release and returns ALLOW or DENY before governed execution for AML, KYC, fraud, dispute review, and customer-impacting recommendation paths.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>Existing financial systems remain in place</h2>
    <p>
      BeaconGuard does not replace case management, transaction systems, analyst authorization, model risk management, or compliance judgment. Those systems remain authoritative. BeaconGuard enforces the request boundary before governed AI, APIs, or automated systems execute.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>Financial scenarios</h2>
    <div class="section-grid section-grid--scenarios">
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>AML / KYC analyst assistance</h3>
        <p><strong>Existing workflow:</strong> Analyst-assist request over case materials.</p>
        <p><strong>Required trusted context:</strong> Workflow identity, analyst role, source-system trust, freshness.</p>
        <p><strong>Control evaluated:</strong> Role and pathway controls in the Compliance Playbook.</p>
        <p><strong>Result:</strong> ALLOW when requirements are satisfied; otherwise DENY.</p>
        <p><strong>Why / When denied:</strong> Missing role, pathway, or approval conditions. An illustrative reason style is <code>APPROVAL_REQUIRED</code>.</p>
        <p><strong>Evidence:</strong> Verifiable Decision Record with release identity.</p>
        <p><strong>Authoritative system:</strong> Case management and AML systems remain authoritative.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Fraud or dispute review</h3>
        <p><strong>Existing workflow:</strong> Dispute or fraud investigation assist.</p>
        <p><strong>Required trusted context:</strong> Request identity, timestamps, approved pathway.</p>
        <p><strong>Control evaluated:</strong> Trust, freshness, and replay checks plus playbook controls.</p>
        <p><strong>Result:</strong> DENY on replay or freshness failure; ALLOW when controls pass.</p>
        <p><strong>Why / When denied:</strong> Replay or freshness checks fail closed before governed execution.</p>
        <p><strong>Evidence:</strong> Verifiable Decision Record for investigation reconstruction.</p>
        <p><strong>Authoritative system:</strong> Fraud and dispute platforms remain authoritative.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Customer-impacting recommendation</h3>
        <p><strong>Existing workflow:</strong> Recommendation that can affect a customer outcome.</p>
        <p><strong>Required trusted context:</strong> Approved pathway and required approval state.</p>
        <p><strong>Control evaluated:</strong> Approval and pathway requirements.</p>
        <p><strong>Result:</strong> DENY when approval is absent.</p>
        <p><strong>Why / When denied:</strong> Required approval is missing. An illustrative reason style is <code>APPROVAL_REQUIRED</code>.</p>
        <p><strong>Evidence:</strong> Verifiable Decision Record; governance review may follow without permitting execution.</p>
        <p><strong>Authoritative system:</strong> Customer operations and compliance remain authoritative.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Production-system automation</h3>
        <p><strong>Existing workflow:</strong> Internal automation acting against production systems.</p>
        <p><strong>Required trusted context:</strong> Environment, role, action, change window, freshness.</p>
        <p><strong>Control evaluated:</strong> Deterministic Playbook Evaluation against the Active Verified Release.</p>
        <p><strong>Result:</strong> ALLOW or DENY before the automation proceeds.</p>
        <p><strong>Evidence:</strong> Verifiable Decision Record for operations and audit review.</p>
        <p><strong>Authoritative system:</strong> Production systems of record remain authoritative.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>What BeaconGuard does not replace</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Case management or transaction processing systems</li>
      <li>Analyst authorization or compliance judgment</li>
      <li>Model risk management programs</li>
      <li>SIEM, IAM, or GRC platforms</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="page-actions">
      <a class="btn-primary" href="mailto:architecture@beaconguardassurance.com?subject=Financial%20Workflow%20Review">Request a Financial Workflow Review</a>
      <a class="btn-secondary" href="/docs/architecture">Review System Architecture</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
